:INFO
The Book I Started, Abandoned, and Finally Loved
I first tried Hyperion in 2019 and stopped after three months. The structure is \
deliberately unusual: six pilgrims on a journey each tell one story, and the \
stories vary so wildly in tone that you can love one and actively dislike the next. \
The Priest's Tale destroyed me. The Detective's Tale bored me. The Poet's Tale \
won me back. I finished the whole thing two years after I started and it is one \
of the books I am most glad I returned to eventually.

